{"title":"Pace Cycles RC429 is a 120 mm Hardtail for Flat or Drop Bars","link":"https://theradavist.com/pace-cycles-rc429/","date":1739458492000,"content":"<p><em>The <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/pace-cycles/\" target=\"_blank\">Pace Cycles</a> RC429 is a shorter travel sibling to the UK brand’s RC529 130-150 mm hardcore hardtail. It’s designed to redefine what’s possible within the short travel hardtail genre. Ride it flat bar or as a <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/drop-bar-29er-mountain-bikes/\" target=\"_blank\">drop-bar 29er</a> and with a 100-130 mm suspension fork or swap on a suspension-corrected rigid fork…</em><span></span></p>\n<h3><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-013.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-013.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-013.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-013.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-013.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-04.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-04.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-04.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-04.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-04.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></h3>\n<h3>Pace Cycles RC429 Quick Hits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Frame £989</li>\n<li>Builds from £3539</li>\n<li>100-130mm travel. So, if you want a longer travel steel hardtail look at our RC529 (130-150mm travel).</li>\n<li>Made with Reynolds 853 steel.</li>\n<li>Drop bar / rigid fork compatible if that’s your game.</li>\n<li>All sizes in stock – medium, large, and extra large</li>\n<li>Colors – Iron Ore Orange, Buck Tail White, and Moss Grey. (Who doesn’t love a Farrow and Ball paint chart).</li>\n<li>Built in Czechia, designed and assembled in-house in North Yorkshire</li>\n<li>Complete builds and custom builds are available.</li>\n<li>All geometry is on the website figures shown with sagged with a rigid fork, 120 and 130mm forks, all sagged.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-07.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-07.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-07.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-07.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-08.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-08.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-08.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-08.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The RC429 is designed to to be an everyday bike or taken out on an extended tour. It has bottle bosses on the seat tube, top and underside of the downtube. Stick to the singletrack or take the rutted gravel road with your choice of cockpit or fork setup, hitting a sweet spot for general trail or gravel riding, the RC429 can change along with your riding routines.</p>\n<h3><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2775\" height=\"1850\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/RC429_new_geometry.jpg?fit=1200,1850&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/RC429_new_geometry.jpg?w=2775&amp;quality=75 2775w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/RC429_new_geometry.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/RC429_new_geometry.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/RC429_new_geometry.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/RC429_new_geometry.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/RC429_new_geometry.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></h3>\n<h3>Geometry</h3>\n<p>Depending on configuration, be it rigid or with a suspension fork, the RC429 comes in a nice middle ground between XC and super progressive with a 65º ish head angle and 75º ish seat angle.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-06.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-06.jpg?w=200&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-06.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-012.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-012.jpg?w=200&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-012.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-011.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-011.jpg?w=200&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-011.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-010.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-010.jpg?w=200&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-010.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-016.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-016.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-016.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Pace-Cycles-RC-429-016.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://pacecycles.com/pages/rc429-new\" target=\"_blank\">Pace Cycles</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/pace-cycles-rc429/\">Pace Cycles RC429 is a 120 mm Hardtail for Flat or Drop Bars</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"cf22da23760666f9b76db1f815a4d49df99756288b24b226052ef33ee3c1079d","category":"Cycling"}